      "body": "**T12 r5: fourth false pinned statement found and repaired \u2014 finite-strata flattening statements need a noetherian base (`IsNoetherian`), not merely locally noetherian.**\n\n- **The defect**: `flatLocusReduction`, `flatLocusAssembly`, `flatteningStratification`, `flatteningStratification_universal`, `.ofCurve` all hypothesised `[IsLocallyNoetherian S]` while concluding a *finite* flat stratification. Counterexample: on $S = \\coprod_{n\\ge 1}\\mathbb A^n$ give component $n$ the coherent sheaf $\\bigoplus_{k\\le n}(i_{V_k})_*\\mathcal O_{V_k}$ for a strictly nested flag $V_1\\supset\\cdots\\supset V_n$; a flat locally-closed stratum through the generic point of $V_k$ cannot contain another level's generic point (local freeness forces relatively clopen intersection with each $V_j$, against the dense lower level), so component $n$ forces $\\ge n+1$ strata and no finite family covers all components. Nitsure and the blueprint's main-theorem body correctly say **noetherian**; the lemma-node bodies and the Lean had drifted to locally noetherian.\n- **Repair** (commit `f2e8a3c67c`): Lean hypotheses strengthened to `IsNoetherian` (Mathlib's loc-noeth + compact class); blueprint bodies of `lem:flat_locus_reduction_lean`, the assembly node and the universal node aligned; the counterexample recorded as a blueprint remark and in the `flatLocusReduction` docstring. The \u2115-indexed $n=0$ case (`flatLocusStratification`) is *correct* at locally noetherian (the fibre rank is the global countable index) and was left unchanged. All existing derivations (`flatteningStratification`/`flatLocusAssembly`/`ofCurve` from Lemma 6) recompile; `lake build` green.\n- **Why it matters**: the next session attacking `flatLocusReduction` (Noetherian induction consuming the now axiom-clean `genericFlatness`) would otherwise have sunk effort into an unprovable statement \u2014 the r2 standing lesson (truth-check long-lived typed sorries before attacking) strikes again; this is its fourth catch in this file.",
