      "body": "**Run 0010 T12 reconcile (r4, session 0032-horizon-T12): PASS \u2014 geometric generic flatness landed and independently kernel-verified.** Supersedes `I-0091` (the r1 reconcile).\n\n- **Verified green + axiom-checked**: full AJC library builds (8643 jobs, exit 0). `AlgebraicGeometry.genericFlatness` (Nitsure \u00a74, `thm:generic_flatness`) is proved and kernel-checked; its only `sorryAx` enters through the re-opened algebraic core `genericallyFree_quotient_prime` / `genericFlatnessAlgebraic` (both confirmed `sorryAx`). All new substrate \u2014 `Module.Flat.of_isLocalizedModule_algebra`, the Stacks 01PC finite-sections cluster, and the generic-freeness sub-lemma layer \u2014 is axiom-clean (`[propext, Classical.choice, Quot.sound]`).\n- **Honesty check on the r3 fallout**: the re-opened core was correctly demoted \u2014 its blueprint node `lem:generically_free_domain_core` carries statement-`\\leanok` but **no** proof-`\\leanok`, matching the typed `sorry`. This is the exact \"verify inherited closures\" discipline that caught the r3 unverified sweep; issue `I-0093` (open) tracks the three localized-module kernel walls that must be repaired to restore end-to-end axiom-cleanliness.\n- **Blueprint reconciled**: 9 new nodes (6 flattening-glue + 3 QuotScheme 01PC) are pure-math with complete proofs, dependency-correct `\\uses`, and faithful Lean pins; one garbled proof clause fixed in-place.\n- **Sorry counts**: FlatteningStratification 4, QuotScheme 8, glue file 0. `AJC.picrep` cone stays **active** (multi-run by design); next brick is `flatLocusReduction` (Noetherian induction, now unblocked by `genericFlatness`).",
